1,3],[1,9,5]]\nOutput: 17\n\n \nConstraints:\n\nm == accounts.length\nn == accounts[i].length\n1 <= m, n <= 50\n1 <= accounts[i][j] <= 100\n\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def maximumWealth(self, accounts: List[List[int]]) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def maximumWealth(self, accounts: List[List[int]]) -> int:\n        # Calculate the wealth of each customer by summing their bank accounts\n        customer_wealths = [sum(customer_accounts) for customer_accounts in accounts]\n        # Return the maximum wealth found\n        return max(customer_wealths)\n```\n\nThis solution calculates the wealth of each customer by summing the values in each sublist of `accounts` and then returns the maximum value from this list of sums.", "estimated_date": 1606608000000}